        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-01 22:50:40.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nJim, have to get familiar with @Property annotation to do the work, but can it do, \"flattened\" hierarchical property naming handling?   Thing here, property name is not fixed .. ie. http.server.services.X.https and http.server.services.Z.https .. \n\nPoint being the property names are unbound and not known a priori.  So, question is if @Property supports such functionality?",
        "patchset_number": 3
